---
// V2 StorySection — two-column layout, clip-path reveal on scroll
---
<section id="story" aria-labelledby="story-heading" class="story-section">
  <div class="story-inner">
    <!-- LEFT: index + label -->
    <div class="story-left" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="story-index">—01—</div>
      <div class="story-label">The Dream</div>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: content -->
    <div class="story-right">
      <blockquote class="story-pullquote v2-reveal" id="story-quote">
        <p>"The most profound hospitality is not about service. It is about place."</p>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="story-body v2-reveal" id="story-body">
        <p>
          Green Horizon is not a hotel in the way you might imagine one. It is a small, deliberate
          collection of rooms and villas on the edge of Strandzha — Bulgaria's last great coastal
          wilderness, where the mountain meets the Black Sea without apology.
        </p>
        <p>
          Four rooms. Six villas. Each oriented to a different quality of light. Each built to stand
          in the landscape rather than above it. The cliff is not a backdrop. It is the point.
        </p>
      </div>

      <a
        href="#journey"
        class="story-cta v2-reveal"
        id="story-cta"
        aria-label="Read the full story of Green Horizon"
      >
        Read the story →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .story-section {
    background: #1F1D18;
    padding: 8rem clamp(2rem, 6vw, 8rem);
  }

  .story-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Left column */
  .story-left {
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .story-index {
    font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 3rem);
    color: #7A8C84;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .story-label {
    font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #7A8C84;
  }

  /* Right column */
  .story-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .story-pullquote {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .story-pullquote p {
    font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: #EAE6DE;
  }

  .story-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .story-body p {
    font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #7A8C84;
  }

  .story-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Manrope', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #A8D5C2;
    text-decoration: none;
    position: relative;
    width: fit-content;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .story-cta::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    bottom: -2px;
    width: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: #A8D5C2;
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
  }

  .story-cta:hover::after {
    width: 100%;
  }

  /* Clip-path reveal */
  .v2-reveal {
    clip-path: inset(100% 0 0 0);
    will-change: clip-path;
  }

  :focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #A8D5C2;
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .story-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }
    .story-left {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 1rem;
      padding-top: 0;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  (function () {
    const prefersReduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches

    const initReveal = () => {
      const g = (window as any).gsap
      const ST = (window as any).ScrollTrigger
      if (!g || !ST) return

      const reveals = document.querySelectorAll('#story .v2-reveal')
      reveals.forEach((el, i) => {
        if (prefersReduced) {
          ;(el as HTMLElement).style.clipPath = 'none'
          return
        }
        g.to(el, {
          clipPath: 'inset(0% 0 0 0)',
          duration: 0.9,
          ease: 'power4.out',
          scrollTrigger: {
            trigger: el,
            start: 'top 88%',
            once: true,
          },
          delay: i * 0.1,
        })
      })
    }

    if ((window as any).gsap && (window as any).ScrollTrigger) {
      initReveal()
    } else {
      window.addEventListener('load', initReveal)
    }
  })()
</script>
